---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";

const stages = [
  {
    title: "Concept → Narrative Pillars",
    subtitle:
      "Establish the emotional architecture and gameplay purpose of each story.",
    description:
      "Example: In Androlynne, the pillars of hope, sacrifice, and corruption informed every environmental and mechanical reaction.",
  },
  {
    title: "Design Documentation → System Translation",
    subtitle:
      "Convert story concepts into actionable design: quest logic, state changes, condition maps, and emotional objectives.",
    description:
      "Deliverables: narrative bibles, tone sheets, branching maps, dialogue flowcharts, and implementation-ready summaries for design teams.",
  },
  {
    title: "Integration → Tools & Prototyping",
    subtitle:
      "Build and iterate narrative systems using tools like Twine or Unreal Blueprint logic.",
    description:
      "Focus on state-based triggers and reactivity loops that make emotional beats tangible.",
  },
  {
    title: "Iteration → Cross-Team Feedback",
    subtitle:
      "Work collaboratively with level design, gameplay, and QA to refine pacing, clarity, and consequence visibility.",
    description:
      "Each iteration tightens the feedback loop between what the player feels and what the world does.",
  },
];

const systemCols = [
  {
    title: "Narrative Trigger",
    items: [
      "Player compassion",
      "Player betrayal",
      "Moral indecision",
      "Emotional exhaustion",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Systemic Translation",
    items: [
      "State variable: empathy +1",
      "State variable: reputation -2",
      "Latent timer triggers",
      "Hidden fatigue metric",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Example Outcome",
    items: [
      "NPCs open new dialogue routes; environment calms",
      "Ally faction AI changes patrol patterns",
      "NPC hesitation dialogue; pacing shift",
      "World lighting fades; music changes dynamically",
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Narrative Systems & Implementation — Annalisa Ard"
  description="How story, design, and systems interlock to create reactivity and consequence."
>
  <section class="section ns-heading">
    <h1>Narrative Systems & Implementation</h1>
  </section>

  <section class="section ns-intro two-col">
    <p class="long-text">
      Narrative design is the craft of making story playable. My
      implementation process focuses on translating emotional arcs into
      mechanical reactivity — ensuring that narrative choices alter gameplay
      state, perception, and consequence. From documentation to tool
      integration, my approach bridges creative intent with systemic function.
    </p>
    <h2 class="ns-subtitle">
      How story, design, and systems interlock to create reactivity and
      consequence
    </h2>
  </section>

  <section class="section ns-process">
    <h2>My Implementation Process</h2>
    <p class="process-lede">
      I treat narrative development as an iterative design pipeline, not a
      linear scriptwriting process. Each stage ensures that creative intent
      survives implementation and becomes meaningful gameplay.
    </p>
    <ol class="stage-list">
      {
        stages.map((s) => (
          <li class="stage">
            <h3>{s.title}</h3>
            <p class="stage-subtitle">{s.subtitle}</p>
            <p class="stage-description">{s.description}</p>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="section ns-systemic">
    <h2>Systemic Design Approach</h2>
    <p class="systemic-lede">
      In my workflow, every narrative decision connects to a system-level
      behavior. This ensures <em>emotional logic = game logic</em>.
    </p>

    <div class="systemic-cols">
      {
        systemCols.map((col) => (
          <div class="systemic-col">
            <h3>{col.title}</h3>
            <ul>
              {col.items.map((item) => (
                <li>{item}</li>
              ))}
            </ul>
          </div>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section ns-closer">
    <p class="closer-lede">
      The goal is always to connect emotional player experience to systemic
      visibility.
    </p>
    <ul class="closer-bullets">
      <li>
        A companion hesitates mid-battle because of trust states, not just
        dialogue flags.
      </li>
      <li>
        A secret faction evolves as a simulation of power, not just a series
        of fetch quests.
      </li>
      <li>
        Lighting changes color just not because of code, but because the
        player made a moral choice.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p class="closer-body">
      That's the heart of my process: transforming emotion into interaction,
      and story into system. My process builds worlds that react, characters
      that remember, and stories that evolve through play — not exposition.
    </p>
    <p class="closer-final">
      Because in the end, the best stories aren't told. They're played.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .ns-heading {
    padding-top: 6vh;
    padding-bottom: 2vh;
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .ns-heading h1 {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .ns-intro {
    padding-top: 2vh;
    padding-bottom: 4vh;
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .ns-intro .long-text {
    max-width: 800px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .ns-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.68em;
    font-weight: 400;
    line-height: 1.4;
    max-width: 800px;
    align-self: flex-start;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .ns-process {
    padding: 8vh 5%;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .ns-process h2 {
    font-size: 2.3em;
    margin-bottom: 0.7em;
  }
  .process-lede {
    font-size: 1.7em;
    line-height: 1.5;
    margin: 0 auto 2em;
    max-width: 1100px;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
  }
  .stage-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0;
    max-width: 1100px;
    display: grid;
    gap: 1.5em;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .stage {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 0.5em;
    padding: 1.5em 1.8em;
    transition: background 0.25s ease, border-color 0.25s ease, transform 0.25s ease;
  }
  .stage:hover {
    background: rgba(137, 122, 225, 0.08);
    border-color: rgba(137, 122, 225, 0.45);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }
  .stage h3 {
    font-size: 1.45em;
    margin: 0 0 0.4em;
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .stage-subtitle {
    font-size: 1.15em;
    margin: 0 0 0.5em;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }
  .stage-description {
    font-size: 1em;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .ns-systemic {
    padding: 6vh 5%;
    max-width: 1280px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
  .ns-systemic h2 {
    font-size: 2.3em;
    margin-bottom: 0.4em;
  }
  .systemic-lede {
    font-size: 1.7em;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
    margin-bottom: 2em;
  }
  .systemic-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-top: 2rem;
  }
  @media (max-width: 800px) {
    .systemic-cols {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
  .systemic-col h3 {
    font-size: 1.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1em;
    padding-bottom: 0.5em;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .systemic-col ul {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .systemic-col li {
    padding: 0.6em 0;
    border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--border);
    font-size: 1.05em;
  }
  .systemic-col li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .ns-closer {
    padding: 6vh 5% 10vh;
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .closer-lede {
    font-size: 1.6em;
    margin-bottom: 1em;
  }
  .closer-bullets {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0 auto 2em;
    max-width: 700px;
    text-align: left;
  }
  .closer-bullets li {
    font-size: 1.15em;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.7em;
    padding-left: 1.5em;
    position: relative;
  }
  .closer-bullets li::before {
    content: "•";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 1.4em;
    line-height: 1;
    top: 0.05em;
  }
  .closer-body {
    font-size: 1.2em;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.92);
  }
  .closer-final {
    font-size: 1.5em;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-top: 2em;
  }
</style>
